xml.description: ## Description PV1 is varied from 0 to 4.5 V in steps of 0.1V . The voltage drop across the diode is measured via A1, and the current flow across it can be measured using the known value of the current limiting resistor (R = 1K) . current = voltage drop across the resistor(PV1-A1) divided by resistance. I = (PV1-A1)/1000 This is plotted on the Y axis, and on the X-Axis is the voltage drop across the diode (= A1) ## Results for a 4148 Diode ## Activities + Find out the IV curves for different diodes, and LEDs + Which colour LED has the highest knee voltage? Why?
